<script>
function startProgram()
{
    var headertext = '<table border="0" width="100%" style="height:16px"><tr><td width="80%"><font style="font-size:smaller" color="#0066cc"><b>Pay In Lieu of Benefits Coverage</b></font></td><td width="10%" align="right" valign="middle"><a href=javascript:self.close()><font color="#0066cc"><b>Close</b></font></a>&nbsp;</td><td width="10%" align="right" valign="middle"><a href=javascript:self.print()><font color="#0066cc"><b>Print</b></font></a>&nbsp;</td></tr></table>'

	
	var html = '<div class="plaintablecell" style="padding:10px">';
	html += '<p>'
	html += 'St. Luke\'s offers Pay In Lieu of Benefits Plan. The pay in lieu of benefits plan (PILB) is an <b><u>OPTIONAL</u></b> benefit election and is designed to allow benefits eligible employees who have health insurance coverage under a non-St. Luke\'s health plan to elect a higher rate of pay in lieu of certain benefits.  You may elect or decline this benefit.<p>'
	html += '<p>'
	html += 'If you choose this option, you are agreeing to <B>FORFEIT</B> the following:<p>'
	html += '<ul><li>Group Health Plan</li><li>Paid Time Off (PTO)</li><li>Extended Sick Leave (ESL)</li><li>Long Term Disability (LTD)</li><li>PTO Donations</li><li>ESL Bonus</li><li>Group Term Life and Supplemental Term Life Insurance</li><li>Adoption Reimbursement</li></ul><p>'
	html += '<p>'
	html += 'You will <b><u>RETAIN</u></b> (based on applicable eligibility and FTE Status) the following St. Luke\'s benefits:<p>'
	html += '<ul><li>Retirement Program</li><li>Flexible Spending Account (FSA)</li><li>Tuition/Certification Reimbursement</li><li>Employee Assistant Program (EAP)</li><li>On-Site Child Care (Little Luke\'s)</li><li>Leave of Absence Program</li><li>E.E. Gilbertson Scholarship</li><li>Workers\' Compensation</li><li>Unemployment Insurance</li><li>All Voluntary Benefits</li><li>Years of Service Awards</li><li>Bereavement Pay</li><li>25% St. Luke\'s Facilities Discount</li></ul><p>'
	html += 'With PILB being an optional election, if you do not elect PILB, you will remain eligible for all applicable benefits based on your employment status.  For example, if you do not want to enroll in St. Luke\’s Group Health Plan, you are not required to elect PILB.<p>'
	html += 'For eligible employees electing pay in lieu of benefits, their base salary will be increased as follows:<p>'
	html += '<table border="0"><tr><td><font size="2">Full-time:</font></td><td><font size="2">(80 hours per pay period)</font></td><td><font size="2">15%</font></td></tr><tr><td><font size="2">Part-time Level 3:</font></td><td><font size="2">(56-79 hours per pay period)</font></td><td><font size="2">12%</font></td></tr><tr><td><font size="2">Part-time Level 2:</font></td><td><font size="2">(32-55 hours per pay period)</font></td><td><font size="2">9%</font></td></tr></table><p>'
	html += '<p><b>PILB Enrollment:</b>  Employees are only eligible to elect (or revoke) PILB within 30 days of their hire or transfer to a benefits-eligible status date, during the designated annual enrollment period, or within 60 days of a qualifying change in status.<p>'
	html += '<p><b>Electing PILB:</b> If you elect PILB during open enrollment, you will be paid out your PTO at the beginning of the plan year. If you elect PILB as a new hire, any PTO you may have earned since your date of hire will be forfeited.  Your extended sick leave (ESL) balance will be frozen as of the elected PILB effective date.  You will no longer accrue any PTO or ESL while you are on PILB, nor will you be able to access your frozen ESL.  <b>Any time off will be without pay.  However, you will not be allowed to take off more time than you would have been granted had you been earning PTO.</b><p>'
	html += '<p><b>Revoking Your Pay in Lieu of Benefits Option (PILB) Election (for annual enrollment only):</b> If you revoke PILB (declining PILB in the present enrollment period if you had elected PILB for the previous enrollment period), the following will occur:<p>'
	html += '<UL><LI>Effective March 24, 2013 (beginning of pay period #7), your base hourly rate will be reduced by the percentage associated with your employment status (Full time - 15%, PTL3 - 12%, or PTL2 - 9%).</LI><LI>Effective March 24, 2013, you will accrue PTO and ESL.  You will also be able to use any accrued PTO and ESL according to St. Luke\’s policies.</LI><LI>Effective April 1, 2013 your Group Term Life Insurance and eligibility will resume.</LI><LI>You will be eligible to apply for Adoption Reimbursement for eligible expenses incurred on or after April 1, 2013.</LI><LI>You may enroll yourself and your eligible dependents in St. Luke\’s Group Health Plan between February 4, 2013, and February 22, 2013.</LI></UL><p>'
	html += '</div>'
	document.getElementById("paneBody").innerHTML = html;
	document.getElementById("paneHeader").innerHTML = headertext
	stylePage();
	document.body.style.visibility = "visible";
}
</script>
